<div id="wrapper"><h2><a href="/output/Page2.asp"><img alt="" height="70" src="../files/images/XM_logo.gif" title="XM London Digital Communication" width="162" /></a></h2><h2><img width="190" alt="Case histories" height="80" border="0" src="/files/images/XM_L3_Clients_histories_shdr.gif" /></h2><p><strong>Platinum Guild</strong></p><p>We were asked to produce an intranet, extranet and global website for the Platinum Guild International.</p><p>Platinum Guild's ambition was the development of a global understanding of platinum as the most desirable and precious of metals.</p><p>The extranet is targeted at the jewellery industry including manufacturers, designers and retailers, and communicates PGI's new branding which has 'water and jewellery' as the theme.<br /><br />The site was launched simultaneously in English, Chinese, German, Indian, Italian and Japanese languages, and was build around our content management system, <a href="http://www.netdevplus.com/" target="_blank">www.netdevplus.com</a>, for in-house administration by the local teams.</p><p>The extranet contains details on PGI and its branding, information about the precious metal, marketing support material, and PR coverage. Visitors can find out about training courses and information, and there is a calendar for key up-and-coming events.</p><p><a href="http://www.platinumguild.com" target="">http://www.platinumguild.com</a></p><p><img alt="Platinum Guild International" border="0" height="195" src="/files/images/XM_L3_histories_PG_a.jpg" width="280" /></p><p><img alt="Platinum Guild International website" border="0" height="195" src="/files/images/XM_L3_histories_PG_b.jpg" width="280" /></p><img class="hide" src="/files/images/clear.gif" width="1" height="1" alt="" />
